# CLASS monorepo

Ponytail still applies, but **reuse project conventions** instead of inventing new ones.

## Layout

| Area | Path | Deploy branch |
|------|------|---------------|
| School dashboard | `src/` | `classroom-app` |
| Admin | `admin-app/` | `admin` |
| User portal | `user-portal-app/` | `user-portal` |
| Tracking | `tracking-app/` | `tracking` |
| Finance | `finance-app/` | `finance` |
| API | `backend/` | `it` (Render) |

## When coding here

- **Match the folder you're in** — imports, i18n (`fr.json` / `en.json`), API clients, component style.
- **React apps:** use existing shadcn/ui components (`Button`, `Input`, etc.) and existing layout patterns.
- **Backend:** extend existing services/repositories; respect `@PreAuthorize`, school scoping, and JPA patterns.
- **Portal roles:** parents = read-only grades; teachers manage grades; don't widen scope silently.
- **SQL maintenance:** add scripts under `scripts/` with preview queries and safe `BEGIN`/`COMMIT` blocks.
- **Git:** commit or push only when the user asks.
- **Question-only tasks:** answer or review — no unsolicited refactors or extra files.
